Easy and delicious. I find the results can vary quite a bit from one batch to another, no doubt depending on the quality of the garlic and other ingredients. Whenever I make this dish, I leave the jalapeno unseeded, increase the cumin to 1 tsp, and reduce the stock to 1.5 cups or less. I often increase the garlic, and if the final dish lacks punch, I add a couple of tsp. each of sherry and red wine/sherry vinegar.

