Rating: 4
I really love this recipe - I've made it several times now. It's easy enough to make for just myself (it's good left over) and good enough to serve to guests as a side dish. If I'm making it for just myself, these beans and rice make a complete meal. I start with cooking 1/2 minced onion in the oil. I use 2 jalapenos, cayenne, ground chipotle and 1-2 t. cumin. I put one can of the beans with some chicken broth in the blender before adding and leave the other can whole - much easier than mashing in the skillet. For me what really pushes this stuff into deliciousness though is the lime juice added at the end. It thickens quite a bit as it cools, so turn off the heat when it still seems too watery. This recipe has become a real favorite of mine. It's cheap to make, healthy and absolutely delicious.

